Deputy Telecommunications Minister Stella Ndabeni Abrahams says it's imperative that issues discussed by delegates are properly communicated. JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC) insists its leaders and members speak with one voice on policy decisions to ensure there's a clear understanding about where the party is heading.On Wednesday, Deputy Telecommunications Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams gave a briefing on the outcomes of the communications commission at the ANC policy conference.She says that it is imperative that issues discussed by delegates are properly communicated.Ndabeni Abrahams says there must be a coherent message communicated by ANC members. It s important that we focus on one message, many voices. However, she says that this doesn't apply to personal issues. The ANC will take action only when members contradict each other on policies. The commission also reaffirmed its position to support media freedom but says media self-regulation should be challenged in parliament.(Edited by Refilwe Pitjeng)